==English==

===Etymology===
From Middle English noun ''[[coppeweb]]'', ''spider web'', from Old English ''[[attercoppe|āttercoppe]]'', ''spider'', from ''[[ator|ātor]]'' (''poison'') and ''[[copp]]'' (''head'').

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''cobweb''', plural '''cobwebs'''
# a [[spider]]’s [[web]], or the [[remain]]s of one
# one of its [[filament]]s; [[gossamer]]
# an [[intricate]] [[plot]]
#{{computing}} a [[web page]] that either has not been [[update]]d for a long time, or that is rarely [[visit]]ed

